  "response": "The average electric bill for a 2-bedroom apartment in the Bay Area can vary significantly based on factors such as location, the size of the apartment, energy efficiency, and personal usage habits. As of the most recent data, residents in the Bay Area can expect their electric bills to range from approximately $75 to $150 or more per month for a 2-bedroom apartment. This estimate can vary, so it is always a good idea to check with local utility providers or current tenants for more specific information.",
